{"id":4200,"date":"2016-12-05T14:21:53","date_gmt":"2016-12-05T22:21:53","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/?p=4200"},"modified":"2016-12-05T14:21:53","modified_gmt":"2016-12-05T22:21:53","slug":"sfi-transitioning-to-new-labels-for-driver-restraints-and-window-netsroll-cage-nets-for-2017","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/sfi-transitioning-to-new-labels-for-driver-restraints-and-window-netsroll-cage-nets-for-2017\/","title":{"rendered":"SFI Transitioning to New Labels for Driver Restraints and Window Nets\/Roll Cage Nets for 2017"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Beginning in\u00a02017, SFI Foundation, Inc. (SFI) is changing the way its labels for Driver Restraints, Window Nets, and Roll Cage Nets are dated.<\/p>\n<p>SFI is implementing a New Label design which will remove the punched-out month\/year date of manufacture and instead incorporate a single expiration date pre-printed on the label. This system will eliminate the need for punch-dating of labels and aims to facilitate technical inspection of dated products in the field.<\/p>\n<p>New Labels will start being used after January 1, 2017. An example of the new label (right), next to the old label (left) for comparison, is shown here:<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4201 size-full\" src=\"http:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/New-and-Old-2017-Labels.png\" alt=\"new-and-old-2017-labels\" width=\"608\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/New-and-Old-2017-Labels.png 608w, https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/New-and-Old-2017-Labels-300x123.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The new labels will be used for the following SFI products:<\/p>\n<p>Driver Restraints: SFI Specs 16.1, 16.2, 16.5, and 16.6<\/p>\n<p>Window Nets: SFI Spec 27.1<\/p>\n<p>Roll Cage Nets: SFI Spec 37.1<\/p>\n<p>Labels will come out in 6-month segments per the below chart. These certified items may still be used for 2 years, the service life has not changed.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4203 size-full\" src=\"http:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/New-Label-Table-1.png\" alt=\"new-label-table\" width=\"389\" height=\"154\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/New-Label-Table-1.png 389w, https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/New-Label-Table-1-300x119.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 389px) 100vw, 389px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Be aware that product manufacturers are allowed to use the discontinued punch-date style labels (above left) until their existing supply runs out. Therefore, you may see the old style labels on Driver Restraints and Window Nets\/Roll Cage Nets for a while. Restraints or Nets with the old label may also still be used until they expire, which is 2 years from the date of manufacture punched on the tag.<\/p>\n<p>Please direct any questions about the new label dating system to the SFI office.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Beginning in\u00a02017, SFI Foundation, Inc. (SFI) is changing the way its labels for Driver Restraints, Window Nets, and Roll Cage Nets are dated. SFI is implementing a New Label design which will remove the punched-out month\/year date of manufacture and instead incorporate a single expiration date pre-printed<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[18,14,6,7,44,1,12,41,15,60,9],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-4200","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-autoracing","category-boatracing","category-dragracing","category-general","category-karting","category-manufacturers","category-news","category-offroadracing","category-specifications","category-technicalsafety","category-tractorpulling"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4200","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=4200"}],"version-history":[{"count":13,"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4200\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":4518,"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4200\/revisions\/4518"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=4200"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=4200"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=4200"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}